		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I didn't miss your point. It's just totally irrelevant.<br><br>They make a perfectly valid observation... if the gear gap between raiders and non-raiders becomes too large it's detrimental to the game. And, yes, it would be.<br>The question is... are we at that point.<br><br>Talking about communism or whatever has no bearing, because like Sony say "you're in our world now". They are the gods/dungeon masters of our game world, they are not like a government... and you, qua your toon, are not like an individual in real life.<br>You did not create, earn, make anything in EQ. You are playing a game. <br>The devs can hopefully create/maintain a game where you get the feeling that you did these things and the game can give you a sense of accomplishment for playing it well. But that's different.<br><br>Btw I'm saying this as a hardcore raider with one of the best geared toons in the game.<p>Message Edited by Naubi on <span class=date_text>12-03-2005</span> <span class=time_text>09:13 PM</span>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
