			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Naubi wrote:<BR>I didn't miss your point. It's just totally irrelevant.<BR><BR>They make a perfectly valid observation... if the gear gap between raiders and non-raiders becomes too large it's detrimental to the game. And, yes, it would be.<BR>The question is... are we at that point.<BR><BR>Talking about communism or whatever has no bearing, because like Sony say "you're in our world now". They are the gods/dungeon masters of our game world, they are not like a government... and you, qua your toon, are not like an individual in real life.<BR>You did not create, earn, make anything in EQ. You are playing a game.<BR><BR>Btw I'm saying this as a hardcore raider with one of the best geared toons in the game.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>If you didn't miss my point, why do you keep bringing up governments, and comparing sony to one? The only reason I ever brought up price controls was just to give an example of an uninformed opinion. I was not saying YOUR opinion was uninformed. What I was saying was that the people running around in 4 expansion old 1 group gear, cannot use their experiences as evidence that the "gear gap" is too large. They wouldn't know. </P>
<P>I am also arguing that the "gear gap" is NOT too large, and in fact, the group player has it better than ever.After all, a warrior can gear out to 11khp, 2100+ac with 1 group gear. That is more than enough to trivalize the vast majority of group encounters. So, if the gear is good enough to not only allow them to complete group events, but to trivialize most of them, why do they need better? The reason they are arguing that the gear gap is too big, is because they have significantly worse gear than the best available, and they are comparing their performance to characters like yours, with high end gear.</P>
<P>But, back to the original topic of this thread, the DODH augments, the devs have already said they were not supposed to be that good, and they are going to nerf them.</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
