Treeslayer wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>&nbsp;</BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>If you didn't miss my point, why do you keep bringing up governments, and comparing sony to one? <BR>
<HR>
</P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>Naubi can provide (her?) own answer I am sure, but there is an easy comparason between SoE and government. Both provide services in return for fees. Both have to keep their citizens/players sufficiently content that they keep the peace and do not rebel either by causing problems within the game, or by leaving for another country/game.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And I think it has been Kyv crying 'marxism'&nbsp;at any&nbsp;suggestion that the playing field not be too imbalanced in EQ, conveniently forgetting that pretty much every capitalist country has progressive taxes rather than flat taxes, and most have at least some sort of old age security and welfare programs to keep the RL 'playing field' from becomming 'too imbalanced.' But that would be economics, not governance.&nbsp;Capitalism and communism are actually economic systems rather than systems of government... </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
