		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Kyvthuhlu wrote:<BR>
<DIV>Actually I'm saying it in a mocking tone implying that people are like the <EM>Fiddler on the Roof</EM> character Perchek who want the wealth of the rich to be distributed amongst the poor - I'm not trying to start big, long debates on the true ideals of Karl Marx or the historical avenues taken by capitalism and communism, I am, rather bluntly, pointing out that the same hysteria that wracked several third world countries and demanded that personal achivement me damned is paraded by people like Jazya.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But no clearly your personal theory is right, I am "crying" it to keep the plebs down so that my equestrian and patrician brothers can live a priviledged life.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>It is just as wrong to suggest that there should be no redistribution of wealth as to say that all the wealth should be redistributed.</P>
<P>In the context of this issue, it is just as wrong to say that the gap between raiders and casuals has to constantly widen as to say there should be no gap at all. </P>
<P>Keeping the gap from getting too big is important. Keeping the gap in place is important. Frankly, though,&nbsp;it is a lot easier to cry 'hysteria' for those that are advantaged than for those that are disadvantaged in that the status quo favours the advantaged (hence the term 'advantaged').</P>
<P>To borrow from a different historic 'redistribution of wealth,' one where it was a capitalist structure both before and after redistribtion, dismissing the issues of keeping the game fun for multiple playstyles is like saying to the casuals 'let them eat cake.'</P>
<P>Again... easier to say when you are not a casual player.</P>
<P>Pouncequick</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>	
