		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<P>
<HR>
To borrow from a different historic 'redistribution of wealth,' one where it was a capitalist structure both before and after redistribtion, dismissing the issues of keeping the game fun for multiple playstyles is like saying to the casuals 'let them eat cake.'
<HR>
</P></DIV>
<P>That would be a valid position if anyone could "inherit" AA's, flags, or gear...but alas, they can't, every single person starts at point A and must work their way up.</P>
<P>
<HR>
Again... easier to say when you are not a casual player.
<HR>
</P>
<P>Meanwhile it's harder to claim that there's a "wide gap" at the moment when Qvic+ gear is coming from single group encounters, with <STRONG>zero</STRONG> previous requirements.</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
