			<blockquote><hr>Even with DoN vendor gear, the top augs are 680 crystals each. That is rather a lot of creator missions (approx 20 each).<hr></blockquote><br><br>40 crystals per creator win<br>takes ~15 minutes or less to complete<br><br>680 / 40 = 17 missions<br><br>17 missions x 15 minutes = 255 minutes = 4.25 hours work<br><br>Thats exactly the same amount of time I raid/play per night.  I don't get gear every night or week either.<br><br>One thing casual groupers have over raiders is that you can do it anytime of the day, whenever you want and can only do 1 a day if you want.<br><br>If you are raiding,  you have to be there every night for 4 hrs and often lose a lot of xp due to learning new encounters, doing backflags over and over and not always winning.  Plus you have to be there for the full 4 hours, you can't usually take a break.<br><br>Now DODH missions give you 200 hp gear, the same gear that drops in QVIC minus the focii, plus you don't have to do hours of backflagging Ikkinz, Uqua...<br><br>So tell me again, why is it so bad?
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							-<br>--<br><a href=http://eq.testmagelo.com/profile/1018594 target="_default">Nedrom the Savior</a>, 75 Iksar Monk  <a href=http://www.clubfu.net target=_default>Club Fu</a>, Bristlebane Server
							</div>
								
