			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=146877#M146877">222</a> of 832
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1142 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Treeslayer wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Pouncequickk wrote:<BR><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Yes, and as I pointed out in a previous post, the devs have already said those augs were a mistake and are being nerfed.&nbsp; He didn't misuse language, his point was that the group augs were better than the raid augs off the boss of the same zone. So he meant there was a gap, in the other direction. </P>
<P>
<HR>
</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Including, as I understand it, scaling down some of the augs which were not quite&nbsp;that powerful. Just because the devs make a change does not mean the change is neccessarily entirely good. After all, if they were incapable of error, the augs would have been fine in the first place. </P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>We usually get one scale per clearing on the Creators, occasionally better on nest missions. Not everyone in the group wants them, so easily 1 per 5 hours. DoN cultural takes from 1 to 3 scales per piece, and one for the augment. That is at MOST 20 hours for a BP and aug (and fail rate is not that high with max smithing + mastery 3 and salvage).</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>Clearing or standard mission run? Even clearing it sounds like you have been much luckier than I in this regard (RNG does not play favourites). I have not been on many runs where people have passed on the scales, do to their bazaar value, and I have heard that there is a 70% success rate cap on the combines... I take it you feel otherwise?</P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>17 actually, or 10 nest missions.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>I have been on blackwing missions with raiders where the mission has failed due to bad luck (or healer or tank being called to a raid and it being too awkward to replace them due to repops). Getting casuals to succeed at that mission (or even attempt it) is not trivial.</P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Again I disagree. We've had all of anguish on farm status for 4 months now, except OMM. I have one anguish loot, not counting augs, and many in my guild still have none. I have gotten TEN total gear pieces in approximately the past 8 months or so. You seriously expect me to believe that a group player, putting in the same amount of time, could not obtain ALL of the DoD arc rewards, and fill out their slots with cultural in that same time? Also allow me to point out that some of those items I have gotten are only 10-30 hp/mana better than the one group stuff. Only ONE item is above 300hp/mana</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>You speak as if you are going straight from casual gear to anguish gear. There is quite a large gap indeed&nbsp;between casual gear and anguish gear. How about the gear obtained against easier targets? Or do you do nothing but twiddle your thumbs between anguish runs?
<HR>
</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Bad attitudes are present in all level of player, not just raid guilders. Honestly, I don't even think they are AS common among my guild, as in the average pickup group.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>As I said, not all raiders are like that, and not all guilds attract or encourage such attitudes. I rather like the one I am in now. That said, I am still a 'recent casual' so perhaps can draw comparasons easier?</P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>It is easy, the gap is NOT too great. The only gap that is too great, is the perception gap. Take RSS for example. I used to heal a 9.5khp BUFFED knight tank there, back when I had about 3 pieces of PoTime gear, and the rest was crap. Now I hear people saying you cannot do RSS with less than a 12k unbuffed tank.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>What was the tank's gear like and what was your gear like? For that matter what was the dps of your party like? Faster kills means less healing (something that too many dismiss when forming groups), and raid gear means better weapons, not just better armour. I agree that some of it is perceptions, but not all of it. As a raider grouping with raiders, you have a good idea of the quality of those you group with and their gear (assuming you group with guildies). Grouping with random people, you often need a higher safety margin.</P>
<P>
<HR>
&nbsp;</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Every zone will be trivialized by someone with better gear. WoS is trivial to someone in Full DoN cultural, just as it is to someone in raid gear. Naturally, since the TOP raid gear is better more content will be trivial to top raiders. But seriously, How many fully anguish+ geared players are there?</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
Eventually that will be true,&nbsp;but the rate at which it happens is part of the gap&nbsp;issue.&nbsp;Also&nbsp;as I said earlier this is not just about anguish gear vs. casual, but raid gear generally vs. casual.&nbsp;</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Pouncequick</P>
<P><BR>&nbsp;</P></BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE>
