			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Nedrom wrote:<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Even with DoN vendor gear, the top augs are 680 crystals each. That is rather a lot of creator missions (approx 20 each).
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR><BR>40 crystals per creator win<BR>takes ~15 minutes or less to complete<BR><BR>680 / 40 = 17 missions<BR><BR>17 missions x 15 minutes = 255 minutes = 4.25 hours work<BR><BR>Thats exactly the same amount of time I raid/play per night. I don't get gear every night or week either.<BR><BR>One thing casual groupers have over raiders is that you can do it anytime of the day, whenever you want and can only do 1 a day if you want.<BR><BR>If you are raiding, you have to be there every night for 4 hrs and often lose a lot of xp due to learning new encounters, doing backflags over and over and not always winning. Plus you have to be there for the full 4 hours, you can't usually take a break.<BR><BR>Now DODH missions give you 200 hp gear, the same gear that drops in QVIC minus the focii, plus you don't have to do hours of backflagging Ikkinz, Uqua...<BR><BR>So tell me again, why is it so bad?<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>How many non-raiders succeed at those missions? As for the 'creator time' add in the time it takes to find and form up groups, as well as turnover issues and I think you will find it takes rather more time than your calculation which assumes a steady group for the entirety. You cannot 'do it anytime of day, whenever you want' as player availablitiy does not work that way. Raids occur in the hours they occur for a reason, namely the majority are available during those times. Casuals face that same issue.</P>
<P>Also as a casual, even something as trivial as a creator mission is not a guaranteed success, plus you often end up 'stuck' in them, because trying to convince other casuals to go anywhere else but the percieved 'best reward' is not trivial.</P>
<P>Pouncequick<BR></P>
