<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Pouncequickk wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Cellan wrote:<BR>
<DIV>The gear gap between raiders and casuals isn't too wide and getting out of hand.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The gear gap between people that don't put much effort to improve their gear and raiders is as big as ever.....but who cares because the fault in that lies with the former.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>The way you word that is that if&nbsp;they do not raid you are not 'put(ing) much effort to improve their gear.' Regardless of the effort it takes to raid, people do not raid because it takes more effort to get gear if you raid, but because past a certain point, it takes less effort to get better gear in that manner. Where that 'certain point' lies is the basis for this discussion.</P>
<P>Pouncequick</P><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV><A href="javascript:view_profile(1145445);" target=_blank>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1145445</A>&nbsp;not a single piece of equipment from raiding at all on my Ranger alt.&nbsp; Just alot of time farming stuff and effort for better gear.&nbsp; And still having some craptacular items that could use alot of improvement, I do not feel that the character is so far behind raiders as people make it out to be, but rather in league with most PoTime geared Rangers.&nbsp; So no, that is not what I am saying that raiding = putting effort into gear, but that putting effort into gear is rather looking around for upgrades and working for them.&nbsp; </DIV><p>Message Edited by Cellan on <span class=date_text>12-04-2005</span> <span class=time_text>02:26 PM</span>	
